The 2021 Abu Dhabi Grand Prix, the final race of the 2021 Formula One World Championship, was held on December 12, 2021, at the Yas Marina Circuit [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0). The race's final laps and the safety car period were highly controversial, leading to debates over the application of the rules and the role of the race director, Michael Masi [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0).

**Specific Reasons for the Safety Car Period**
The safety car was deployed on lap 53 after Nicholas Latifi crashed his Williams into the Turn 14 barriers [formula1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1) [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0). At the time of the crash, Lewis Hamilton led Max Verstappen by approximately 11 seconds [formula1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1). Mercedes chose not to pit Hamilton, as doing so would have conceded track position to Verstappen [formula1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1). Red Bull, however, used the opportunity to pit Verstappen for soft tires [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0) [formula1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1). After Verstappen's pit stop, five lapped cars (Lando Norris, Fernando Alonso, Esteban Ocon, Charles Leclerc, and Sebastian Vettel) were between him and Hamilton [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0).

**Controversies Surrounding the Safety Car Period**
The primary controversy stemmed from Race Director Michael Masi's handling of the safety car period and the subsequent restart of the race [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0). Key points of contention included:
*   **Partial Lapped Cars Un-Lapping:** Initially, lapped cars were told they would not be allowed to un-lap themselves [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0). Then, with two laps remaining, Masi directed only the five cars between Hamilton and Verstappen to un-lap themselves [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0) [formula1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1) [crash](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-2). This decision allowed Verstappen to close up directly behind Hamilton [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0).
*   **Restart Procedure:** Article 48.12 of the sporting regulations states that "once the last lapped car has passed the leader, the Safety Car will return to the pits at the end of the following lap" [formula1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-1). However, Masi ended the safety car period and restarted the race on the same lap that the cars were allowed to un-lap themselves [crash](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-2). This decision allowed for one final lap of racing [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0).
*   **Alleged Rule Violations:** The FIA's report acknowledged that Masi did not adhere to the regulations, specifically Article 48.12, which required the safety car to complete an additional lap after the last lapped car passed the leader before returning to the pits [tntsports](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-3). Masi also bypassed the standard procedure by resuming the race on the very next lap instead of completing another full lap behind the safety car once the lapped cars had repositioned themselves [indiatimes](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-4).

**Rules and Procedures Called Into Question**
Several regulations and procedures were questioned because of the events in Abu Dhabi [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0):
*   **Safety Car Regulations:** The ambiguity in the wording of the regulations, particularly regarding the discretion afforded to the race director in deploying and withdrawing the safety car, was highlighted [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0). The rule stating "any" lapped cars may unlap themselves was changed to "all" lapped cars must unlap themselves [formula1](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-5) [crash](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-2) [si](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-6).
*   **Role of the Race Director:** Masi's authority and decision-making process came under scrutiny, with many questioning whether his decisions were impartial and in line with the regulations [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/2-0).
